BRIDGEPORTâ€”First responders checked on their colleagues Friday evening after an ambulance and another vehicle crashed into each other, according to police dispatch reports.
The ambulance workers were unhurt in the accident, police reported from the scene, near the intersection of Lindley Street and Capital Avenue.
The crash occurred around 8:30 p.m. Friday evening when a car pulled in front of the ambulance, according to AMR spokeswoman Kim Warth. No patient was inside the vehicle, as it was being dispatched to respond to a call.
Police were called to the scene and investigated.
